sentences: Ethel V. Finnie (January 7, 1898 – May 1, 1981) was an American classic female blues singer.
Her most notable recording is "You're Gonna Wake Up Some Morning, but Your Papa Will Be Gone".

Finnie married the pianist and composer Porter Grainger on September 25, 1923, in Stamford, Connecticut, with whom she performed throughout the northeastern United States, appearing at various venues and performing on radio programs, as documented in the pages of the African-American press of the period.
She was involved in the sorority Iota Phi Lambda, serving as its southwestern regional director of during the 1950s.
She also served as the treasurer of the Fourth Region of the National Council of Negro Women in the 1960s.
Finnie died in New Orleans on May 1, 1981, aged 83.
She recorded eight songs in 1923 and 1924, including "You're Gonna Wake Up Some Morning, but Your Papa Will Be Gone".
